I get asked all the time, what makes the #powerdot better than all of the different brands of muscle stim machines?? Honestly the convenience of it is probably the biggest difference for me. The fact that there are no wires connected to the device makes it so much easier to pop on and off. It's app based so updates mean more programs and very easy to change levels or resistance by just double clicking back to the app. I use mine for warm up/ recovery, strength or any tweaks of injuries. If you are training hard like an athlete then your recovery should match your training. There's no magic in it, it's just another recovery tool but it's one of my favorites. If you don't know what electric muscle stimulation is, google it 😜 jk but head over to powerdot.com for info. My quads can use all of the help they can get 😁 grow already 🙄 #recovery #calstrength #warmup #mypowerdot #cybermonday don't say I didn't try to warn you on this discount 😘

Guys, if there is anything I ask of you its this. Please do not support this kind of animal cruelty. DO NOT RIDE ELEPHANTS! They are tortured until their "spirits are broken" and they do whatever they want them to do. They are stabbed, beat, and tortured until they give up and stop fighting. This is done to them when they are babies.  It broke my heart to see the rescued elephants at the sanctuary.  Do not support elephant tourism, instead go visit them at sanctuaries to give them some love and have the money go to rehabilitating them. Spread the message and if you already did it, it's ok. Most people don't know what they go through for their entertainment. 😢🐘 #elephanttourism #southeastasia #sayno #elephantjunglesanctuary @elephantjunglesanctuary #bethechange

It may not be where I end, but it is where I began.💕I stepped foot into  Crossfit San Diego at age 14 not wanting to do crossfit for a second, so I did it barefoot and in pjs that day. "How would anyone want to just do this for fun!" I asked myself. The moment I went to a @provinggroundscomps competition to watch my dad @billynation I realized these girls are badass, they look strong and are beautiful!  @jackie585 @emilybridgers @laurenfisher Crossfit changed my life and made me the lady I am today. I used to be shy to the point I wouldn't order my own food at a restaurant, I was making the wrong choices in school I was in transition of finding who I was. In Crossfit San Diego I found myself; who I was and I started to realize I'm capable of a lot more than I think. This gym is now @crossfitinvictus and a huge beautiful location but it will always be CFSD to me. I walked out of this gym a 17 year old a strong independent women who learned how to stand up for herself and to never sell herself short. Did I get my first muscle up here? did I break a 100lb snatch here? No. but I gained myself. It was a huge step emotionally to leave the only gym I knew behind but as a door closes another one opens and I never expected to be as warm as @crossfit_collaboration. Did I get my first muscle here? Yes. Did I break a #100 snatch here? Yes. Does that mean I love this gym more because I was able to break PRs? No, it means that walking into this gym I learned to push myself I learned that saying I can't wasn't an option. When one door closes you retain and you keep your experience close. When the other door opens you sprint in and take what you can as you run though. @crossfit_collaboration is my home. @crossfitsd was my awakening. I stand here in the adult world now and I look back and am proud of everything I have learned about myself and what I can do in the gym and I smile because I know its just beginning. #crossfit #livechanging #impact @crossfit
